# 🐧 Linux Commands for DevOps (Detailed Guide)

This contains essential Linux commands used in real-world DevOps tasks. Each section includes practical commands with explanations.

---

# 📁 1. File & Directory Management

## 🔹 Basic Navigation

```bash
pwd              # Show current directory
ls               # List files
ls -l            # Detailed list (permissions, owner, size)
ls -a            # Show hidden files
cd /path         # Change directory
cd ..            # Move one level up
```

## 🔹 File Operations

```bash
touch file.txt          # Create file
mkdir folder            # Create directory
rm file.txt             # Delete file
rm -rf folder           # Delete folder recursively
cp file1 file2          # Copy file
mv file1 file2          # Rename/move file
```

---

# 🔐 2. File Permissions & Ownership

## 🔹 Check Permissions

```bash
ls -l
```

## 🔹 Change Permissions

```bash
chmod 755 file.sh       # Owner full, others read+execute
chmod +x script.sh      # Make executable
```

## 🔹 Change Ownership

```bash
chown user file.txt
chown user:group file.txt
```

---

# 👥 3. Users & Groups

## 🔹 User Management

```bash
useradd devuser
passwd devuser
usermod -aG sudo devuser
```

## 🔹 Group Management

```bash
groupadd devgroup
usermod -aG devgroup devuser
```

## 🔹 Check Users

```bash
whoami
id
cat /etc/passwd
```

---

# ⚙️ 4. Process Management

## 🔹 View Processes

```bash
ps aux
top
htop
```

## 🔹 Kill Process

```bash
kill PID
kill -9 PID
```

## 🔹 Background Jobs

```bash
sleep 100 &
jobs
fg %1
bg %1
```

---

# 🌐 5. Networking Commands

## 🔹 Check IP & Network

```bash
ip a
hostname -I
```

## 🔹 Connectivity

```bash
ping google.com
curl google.com
wget https://example.com
```

## 🔹 Ports & Services

```bash
netstat -tulnp
ss -tulnp
```

---

# 📦 6. Package Management

## 🔹 Ubuntu/Debian

```bash
apt update
apt upgrade
apt install nginx
apt remove nginx
```

## 🔹 RHEL/CentOS

```bash
yum install nginx
dnf install nginx
```

---

# 🧠 7. Bash Scripting

## 🔹 Simple Script

```bash
#!/bin/bash
echo "Hello DevOps"
```

## 🔹 Run Script

```bash
chmod +x script.sh
./script.sh
```

